    <body><div type="letter">
      <p>St James' Sqre Friday Afternoon</p>
      <p>I am in a disagreeable plight rather. I have not been able to stir all day, waiting for Dr Locock, [parenthetical bracket crossed out] whom it was very necessary I should see on account of a local complaint, of which I have thought nothing hitherto; but finding it become worse, I wished to consult him about it; &amp; he finds, after making a complete examination internally, that I am in a most sad state, requiring great care.</p>
      <p>My general state of health he is quite delighted with; but this disorder might affect that, if it were not seen to. It is one of decided debility, he says.</p>
      <p>I believe that at present I must not ride at all.</p>
      <p>Some light has been</p>
      <p>thrown on my sexual inabilities, by the present circumstances.</p>
      <p>I shall probably remain on in Town 2 or 3 days, on account of this matter; that Dr L-- may watch the first effects of his remedies, which are pretty strong ones. It is sadly inconvenient; for I have to apply things many times a day.--</p>
      <p>I am very well, but not very strong; &amp; quite unequal to hurrying a crowd of business into a day or two; so if I do stay on, I can at least do at leisure, a few things I must otherwise have left undone.</p>
      <p>You will perceive I have been able yet to do nothing about the presents, as I did not succeed yesterday.--</p>
      <p>I really must mind this matter, or else I may be laid up like Miss Martineau perhaps. The womb and everything is in a state of extreme relaxation &amp; tenderness it seems. No muscular tension in any part.--</p>
      <p>If you would not object to forwarding on this letter to William, by post tonight, (to Ockham), it will save my writing the same thing twice over, &amp; I shall mention in my letter to him, that he will find the particulars in one you will send him.--</p>
      <p>Dr L-- thinks my head &amp; all that, now perfectly right; &amp; advises the continuance of wine, as indeed absolutely necessary, (in such quantities that is, as he</p>
      <p>authorizes). My present uterine state does not show any great strength, he says, in the general system.</p>
    </div></body>
